quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,27,"He wishes to turn towards you in mercy, but those who follow their own passions want you to drift far away from the right path"
  4,28,"God wishes to lighten your burdens, for, man has been created weak"
  4,29,"Believers, do not wrongfully consume each other's wealth, but trade with it by mutual consent. Do not kill one another, for God is most merciful to you"
  4,30,"If anyone does these things through transgression and injustice, We shall cast him into the Fire; and that is easy for God"
  4,31,"If you shun the great sins you have been forbidden, We shall cancel out your minor misdeeds and admit you to a place of honour"
  4,32,"Do not covet the bounties which God has bestowed more abundantly on some of you than on others. Men shall be rewarded according to their deeds, and women shall be rewarded according to their deeds. You should rather ask God for His bounty. God has knowledge of all things"
  4,33,"We have appointed heirs for everything that parents and close relatives leave behind. As for those with whom you have entered into agreements, let them, too, have their due. God is witness to all things"